<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - FRONT DRIVE AXLE: SPICER S-9000 - AXLE SHAFT REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>AXLE SHAFT REMOVAL</title>
        <para>Use
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0200975">Figure 75</hotlnk>
            as a reference to remove axle shafts.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0200975" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0200975" filename="../figg02/g0200975.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 75. Axle Shaft Reference</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. Outer Shaft</callout1>
                <callout1>2. Cross Assembly, U-Joint</callout1>
                <callout1>3. Bearing Race, U-Joint</callout1>
                <callout1>4. Snap Ring</callout1>
                <callout1>5. Inner Shaft</callout1>
                <callout1>6. Oil Seal</callout1>
                <callout1>7. Housing Bushing</callout1>
                <callout1>8. Grease Retainer</callout1>
                <callout1>9. Bearing Cup</callout1>
                <callout1>10. Bearing Cone</callout1>
                <callout1>11. Oil Seal</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After knuckle assembly has been removed, the axle shaft and joint assembly can be pulled (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200976">Figure 76</hotlnk>). To remove the axle shaft assembly, hold shaft level and
                pull straight out to avoid damaging the inner oil seal (Item 6,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200975">Figure 75</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200976" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200976" filename="../figg02/g0200976.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 76. Pull Axle Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect housing bushing and oil seal. If replacement is necessary, remove with suitable
                puller (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200977">Figure 77</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200977" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200977" filename="../figg02/g0200977.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 77. Inspect Housing Bushing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect bearing cone, cup and seal (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200978">Figure 78</hotlnk>). Use suitable bearing drive if replacement is necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200979">Figure 79</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200978" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200978" filename="../figg02/g0200978.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 78. Inspect Bearing Cone, Cup and Seal</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0200979" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200979" filename="../figg02/g0200979.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 79. Using Driver</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
